<h1 class="sectionedit1"><a name="stratuslab_release_v02" id="stratuslab_release_v02">StratusLab Release v0.2</a></h1>
<div class="level1">

<p>

Incremental release of StratusLab adding the following features:
</p>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Proxy server enabling:</div>
<ul>
<li class="level2"><div class="li"> secure connection to the cloud</div>
</li>
<li class="level2"><div class="li"> x509/grid certificate authentication</div>
</li>
<li class="level2"><div class="li"> signing and validation of image manifest</div>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Local and private IP address assignment</div>
</li>
</ul>

</div>

<h1 class="sectionedit2"><a name="stratuslab_release_v01" id="stratuslab_release_v01">StratusLab Release v0.1</a></h1>
<div class="level1">

<p>

StratusLab releases first open source cloud solution designed for the
grid.
</p>

<p>
The StratusLab project has released the first version of its cloud
computing distribution which aims to provide a full cloud solution
for grid and cluster computing.
</p>

<p>
The release is a technology preview and not yet production-ready, but it
will give system administrators and users a chance to try out the new
features of what will become an integrated solution for cloud management
and running grid services within the cloud.
</p>

<p>
This StratusLab release contains the following:

</p>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> OpenNebula: virtual machine management</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Web Monitor: administrator dashboard for cloud</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> User CLI: Python-based command line tools for remote access to cloud</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> System Admin. CLI: Command line tools to facilitate installation and management</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Manual and Automated (Quattor) Installation</div>
</li>
</ul>

</div>

<h2 class="sectionedit3"><a name="installation" id="installation">Installation</a></h2>
